        "article": "In the FIFA World Cup, Brazil will take on Norway in the Round of 16 match in New Jersey at 1.30 AM Indian Time tonight. England will face Mexico in Mexico City in the other pre-quarterfinal at 5.30 AM tomorrow. This morning, France booked their place in the quarter-finals with a 1-nil victory over Paraguay in the Round of 16 at Philadelphia. French Captain Kylian Mbappé scored the only goal of the match from the penalty spot in the 70th minute after VAR awarded France a spot-kick. In the other pre-quarterfinal, Morocco registered a commanding 3-nil victory over Canada in Houston to book a place in last eight.",
